---
import ChevronLeft from "@icons/ChevronLeft.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import P from "@components/P.astro";
---

<Layout title="Shlok Desai | Academic Mentor CS 544">
  <div class="flex justify-center max-w-7xl gap-x-16 mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block">
      <button
        onclick="history.back();"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base"
      >
        <ChevronLeft size={16} />
         cd . .
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="main" class="max-w-2xl w-full">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 class="text-gray12 tracking-wider">
          Academic Mentor for CS 544{" "}
          <span class="text-gray11 font-light">@ UW-Madison</span>
        </h1>

        <button
          onclick="history.back();"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base xl:hidden"
        >
          <ChevronLeft size={16} />
           cd . .
        </button>
      </div>

      <span class="text-gray11 font-light text-sm mt-4 block">
        Madison, WI â€¢ 04/2023 - Present
      </span>

      <P className="mt-8">
        CS 400 is the third course in The University of Wisconsin-Madison's
        programming fundamentals sequence. This course introduces balanced
        search trees, graphs, graph traversal algorithms, hash tables and sets,
        and complexity analysis and about classes of problems that require each
        data type. Additional topics include inheritance and polymorphism;
        anonymous inner classes, lambda functions, performance analysis to
        discover and optimize critical code blocks.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-8">Responsibilites:</P>

      <ul class="mt-4 list-disc text-gray11">
        <li>
          <P>One-on-one tutoring for students taking CS 400 on request.</P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Help students debug code and brainstorm solutions for their
            projects.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Help students understand course material, explain concepts, and
            provide sessions on exam prep.
          </P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Collaborate with course Professors deliver positive experiences.
          </P>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="pt-4"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block"></div>
  </div>
</Layout>
